<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>There is no option to give an single element an html attribute, i.e. class for layouting.</p>

<p>In my situation i tried to create an select with default option, and i would like to add some html attributes to it, i.e. class.</p>

    </div>
</div>

<div class="comments">
    <h3>Comments</h3>

    <div class="comment">
        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2009-03-31T06:35:35.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>formSelect()'s third argument, $attribs, let's you do precisely this:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
echo $this-&gt;formSelect('foo', '', array('class' =&gt; 'foobar'), $options);
</code></pre>

<p>which will set the 'class' attribute of the select to 'foobar'.</p>

<p>You cannot set the class for individual options within the select, but that's an edge case we really cannot support.</p>

        </div>
